<br>
At The Overthere, I ran to some ruins and found three Berzerkers inside.  I snared them all and AoE'd them with ease.  I've tri-kited before, but this was the first really easy tri-kite.  <br>
<br>
I'm finding I may have to finish one, two, or even all three separately.  I did succeed in a full quad-kite and then saw the cockatrice slowly coming up from way behind.  Apparently, I had lost that by nuking it until it stopped.  I finished two at once, then the last but didn't see the birdie still undead.  I was OOM by then.  It ran to the guards.  Ugh.<br>
<br>
I've also begun not snaring and kiting for single kites.  I simply nuke, run until my staff of temperate flux tells me I'm out of range, run a bit more, stop, pause, nuke.  I don't even turn around.  I start running immedately after the nuke goes off.  This process saves me the mana I would have spent on a snare attempt.  That's half a big nuke.  I can usually squeeze out one last kill this way if I have two bubbles of mana left.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubicrius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bicrius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/01 2:02:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://students.hamilton.edu/2002/bschulte/eqpics/bic_gin_sm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Almost 39</span><hr size=1> Do yourselves a favor... don't quad in OT, it's harder there and there are too many wandering mobs. I just wrote this up based on what I did from level 34-44, and I hope it helps. Give it a look see:<br>
